Tyson Fury has pulled out of his fight with Alexander Ustinov after his uncle was taken ill.

Fury had been due to fight Ustinov on Saturday evening but pulled out of the heavyweight clash after his uncle and former trainer Hughie was taken to hospital on Saturday morning.

In a statement released by Queensberry Promotions, Hughie was said to be 'seriously ill' and Fury's camp therefore took the decision to 'pull him out of the fight rather than risk his health by sending him into the right with his mind not focused.' It is not clear what Hughie's condition is. 

